Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteBNet(25.10)                                            deleteBNet(25.10)

Name
       deleteBNet  - Given a bussed net or a single bit of a bussed net, logi-
       cally removes the entire bussed net from a design

Syntax
        deleteBNet

       [-help]

       [-moduleBased <moduleName>]

       {-bus busName | -busFromBit <busBitName>}

       Given a bussed net or a single bit of a bussed net,  logically  removes
       the entire bussed net from a design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deleteBNet.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteBNet

       -moduleBased <moduleName>
              Specifies the module name that contains the bus net which  needs
              to be deleted.

              This parameter is optional.

       -bus <busName>
              Specifies  the  base  name of the top-level bus net, or the base
              name of a bus net in verilog module when used with  -moduleBased
              option

       -busFromBit <busBitName>
              Specifies the bus bit name of a top level or a non-top level bus
              net,  or a bus bit name of a bus net in verilog module when used
              together with the -moduleBased option.

       The deleteBNet command does not support wildcards.

       It is not possible to delete a single bit of a bussed  net.  To  change
       the  bus  width of an existing net, the net needs to be deleted and re-
       created with addNet.

Examples
Non-top level bus net
              *

                The following command deletes the bus net x/y/z.

                deleteBNet -busFromBit x/y/z[2]

              * The following command deletes a bus net from a verilog module,
                used with -moduleBased and -busFromBit <busBitName>.

                deleteBNet -busFromBit z[2] -moduleBased Y

              * The following command deletes a bus net from a verilog module,
                used with -moduleBased and -bus <busName>.

                deleteBNet -bus z -moduleBased Y

Top level bus net
              *

                The following command deletes the top-level bus net, using the
                option -busFromBit <busBitName>.

                deleteBNet -busFromBit x[2]

              * The following command deletes the top-level bus net, using the
                option -bus <busName>.

                deleteBNet -bus x

Related Information
